{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":721,"text":"A computer is an incredibly powerful means"},{"time":3388,"text":"of creative expression,"},{"time":5042,"text":"but for the most part,"},{"time":6613,"text":"that expression is confined to the screens"},{"time":8778,"text":"of our laptops and mobile phones."},{"time":11196,"text":"And I'd like to tell you a story about"},{"time":13396,"text":"bringing this power of the computer"},{"time":15352,"text":"to move things around and interact with us"},{"time":17722,"text":"off of the screen and into the physical world"},{"time":20635,"text":"in which we live."}]},{"cues":[{"time":21824,"text":"A few years ago, I got a call from"},{"time":23442,"text":"a luxury fashion store called Barneys New York,"},{"time":25928,"text":"and the next thing I knew,"},{"time":27192,"text":"I was designing storefront kinetic sculptures"},{"time":29885,"text":"for their window displays."}]},{"cues":[{"time":31277,"text":"This one's called \"The Chase.\""},{"time":32672,"text":"There are two pairs of shoes,"},{"time":34018,"text":"a man's pair and a woman's pair,"},{"time":35643,"text":"and they play out this slow, tense chase"},{"time":38547,"text":"around the window"},{"time":39825,"text":"in which the man scoots up behind the woman"},{"time":42050,"text":"and gets in her personal space,"},{"time":43623,"text":"and then she moves away."},{"time":45558,"text":"Each of the shoes has magnets in it,"},{"time":47399,"text":"and there are magnets underneath the table"},{"time":49402,"text":"that move the shoes around."}]},{"cues":[{"time":51366,"text":"My friend Andy Cavatorta was building"},{"time":53398,"text":"a robotic harp for Bjork's Biophilia tour"},{"time":56940,"text":"and I wound up building the electronics"},{"time":59332,"text":"and motion control software"},{"time":61521,"text":"to make the harps move and play music."},{"time":63987,"text":"The harp has four separate pendulums,"},{"time":65998,"text":"and each pendulum has 11 strings,"},{"time":68124,"text":"so the harp swings on its axis and also rotates"},{"time":70612,"text":"in order to play different musical notes,"},{"time":72815,"text":"and the harps are all networked together"},{"time":74977,"text":"so that they can play the right notes"},{"time":76777,"text":"at the right time in the music."}]},{"cues":[{"time":79403,"text":"I built an interactive chemistry exhibit"},{"time":81827,"text":"at the Museum of Science and Industry in Chicago,"},{"time":84426,"text":"and this exhibit lets people use physical objects"},{"time":87407,"text":"to grab chemical elements off of the periodic table"},{"time":90443,"text":"and bring them together to cause"},{"time":91851,"text":"chemical reactions to happen."},{"time":93617,"text":"And the museum noticed that people"},{"time":95541,"text":"were spending a lot of time with this exhibit,"},{"time":97767,"text":"and a researcher from a science education center"},{"time":100914,"text":"in Australia decided to study this exhibit"},{"time":103719,"text":"and try to figure out what was going on."},{"time":105959,"text":"And she found that the physical objects"},{"time":108252,"text":"that people were using were helping people"},{"time":109916,"text":"understand how to use the exhibit,"},{"time":111930,"text":"and were helping people learn in a social way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":114873,"text":"And when you think about\nit, this makes a lot of sense,"},{"time":117139,"text":"that using specialized physical objects"},{"time":119379,"text":"would help people use an interface more easily."},{"time":122651,"text":"I mean, our hands and our minds are optimized"},{"time":125490,"text":"to think about and interact with tangible objects."},{"time":128759,"text":"Think about which you find easier to use,"},{"time":130821,"text":"a physical keyboard or an onscreen keyboard"},{"time":133140,"text":"like on a phone?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":135240,"text":"But the thing that struck me"},{"time":136265,"text":"about all of these different projects"},{"time":138264,"text":"is that they really had to be built from scratch,"},{"time":141381,"text":"down to the level of the electronics"},{"time":143171,"text":"and the printed circuit boards and"},{"time":144277,"text":"all the mechanisms all the way up to the software."},{"time":147022,"text":"I wanted to create something"},{"time":148784,"text":"where we could move objects\nunder computer control"},{"time":152103,"text":"and create interactions around that idea"},{"time":154352,"text":"without having to go through this process"},{"time":156567,"text":"of building something from scratch"},{"time":157950,"text":"every single time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":159325,"text":"So my first attempt at this"},{"time":161316,"text":"was at the MIT Media Lab"},{"time":163000,"text":"with Professor Hiroshi Ishii,"},{"time":164581,"text":"and we built this array of"},{"time":166416,"text":"512 different electromagnets,"},{"time":168673,"text":"and together they were able to move objects around"},{"time":171300,"text":"on top of their surface."},{"time":172836,"text":"But the problem with this"},{"time":174384,"text":"was that these magnets"},{"time":176040,"text":"cost over 10,000 dollars."},{"time":178200,"text":"Although each one was pretty small,"},{"time":179866,"text":"altogether they weighed so much"},{"time":181575,"text":"that the table that they were on"},{"time":182830,"text":"started to sag."},{"time":184388,"text":"So I wanted to build something"},{"time":185720,"text":"where you could have this kind of interaction"},{"time":187336,"text":"on any tabletop surface."}]},{"cues":[{"time":189979,"text":"So to explore this idea,"},{"time":192060,"text":"I built an army of small robots,"},{"time":194210,"text":"and each of these robots has\nwhat are called omni wheels."},{"time":196975,"text":"They're these special wheels"},{"time":198280,"text":"that can move equally easily in all directions,"},{"time":200946,"text":"and when you couple these robots"},{"time":203535,"text":"with a video projector,"},{"time":205445,"text":"you have these physical tools"},{"time":207253,"text":"for interacting with digital information."},{"time":210153,"text":"So here's an example of what I mean."},{"time":211995,"text":"This is a video editing application"},{"time":213917,"text":"where all of the controls"},{"time":215403,"text":"for manipulating the video are physical."},{"time":217710,"text":"So if we want to tweak the color,"},{"time":219292,"text":"we just enter the color mode,"},{"time":220644,"text":"and then we get three different dials"},{"time":221940,"text":"for tweaking the color,"},{"time":223318,"text":"or if we want to adjust the audio,"},{"time":225279,"text":"then we get two different dials\nfor that, these physical objects."},{"time":228620,"text":"So here the left and right channel stay in sync,"},{"time":231466,"text":"but if we want to, we can override that"},{"time":233209,"text":"by grabbing both of them at the same time."},{"time":236208,"text":"So the idea is that we get the speed"},{"time":238136,"text":"and efficiency benefits of using these physical dials"},{"time":241253,"text":"together with the flexibility and versatility"},{"time":244043,"text":"of a system that's designed in software."}]},{"cues":[{"time":247374,"text":"And this is a mapping application"},{"time":249309,"text":"for disaster response."},{"time":251436,"text":"So you have these physical objects"},{"time":253381,"text":"that represent police, fire and rescue,"},{"time":255608,"text":"and a dispatcher can grab them"},{"time":257161,"text":"and place them on the map"},{"time":258487,"text":"to tell those units where to go,"},{"time":260476,"text":"and then the position of the units on the map"},{"time":262852,"text":"gets synced up with the position"},{"time":264821,"text":"of those units in the real world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":268448,"text":"This is a video chat application."},{"time":270060,"text":"It's amazing how much emotion you can convey"},{"time":272412,"text":"with just a few simple movements"},{"time":273625,"text":"of a physical object."}]},{"cues":[{"time":276050,"text":"With this interface, we open up\na huge array of possibilities"},{"time":279102,"text":"in between traditional board games"},{"time":281180,"text":"and arcade games,"},{"time":282594,"text":"where the physical possibilities of interaction"},{"time":285141,"text":"make so many different styles of play possible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":288854,"text":"But one of the areas that I'm most excited"},{"time":291243,"text":"about using this platform for"},{"time":293057,"text":"is applying it to problems that are difficult"},{"time":295600,"text":"for computers or people to solve alone."},{"time":297854,"text":"One example of those is protein folding."},{"time":300476,"text":"So here we have an interface"},{"time":301888,"text":"where we have physical handles onto a protein,"},{"time":305402,"text":"and we can grab those handles"},{"time":307153,"text":"and try to move the protein and\ntry to fold it in different ways."},{"time":310140,"text":"And if we move it in a way that\ndoesn't really make sense"},{"time":313140,"text":"with the underlying molecular simulation,"},{"time":315107,"text":"we get this physical feedback where we can"},{"time":317309,"text":"actually feel these physical handles"},{"time":319282,"text":"pulling back against us."},{"time":320890,"text":"So feeling what's going on"},{"time":322421,"text":"inside a molecular simulation"},{"time":324660,"text":"is a whole different level of interaction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":327606,"text":"So we're just beginning to explore"},{"time":330587,"text":"what's possible when we use software"},{"time":333098,"text":"to control the movement"},{"time":334589,"text":"of objects in our environment."},{"time":336832,"text":"Maybe this is the computer of the future."},{"time":339736,"text":"There's no touchscreen."},{"time":341352,"text":"There's no technology visible at all."},{"time":343383,"text":"But when we want to have a video chat"},{"time":345227,"text":"or play a game"},{"time":346688,"text":"or lay out the slides to our next TED Talk,"},{"time":349401,"text":"the objects on the table come alive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":351674,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":353026,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}